0 MacBooks that are leased with CompNow for student use (CompNow provides support). \n•	6 Windows Desktop PCs that are mainly used for administration.\n•	The server is Windows Server 2012 R2 Standard. There’s a Sentral Server and Oliver Server for Library. \n•	There are 4 smartboards (3 fixed + 1 mobile) and 4 Projectors.\n•	4x Printers are also on lease and do not need any IT Support/Maintenance. \n•	7 WAPs installed, some are POE others are not. \n\nStakeholder Name	Job Position\nDon Leys	Principal\nRebekah Chaudhary	Deputy Principal\nAnna Panova	Office Manager\nGeorg Panov	IT Support (1st level)\n\nBusiness Sponsor:\n	Rebekah Chaudhary (Deputy Principal)\n\nIT Support (1st level)\n	George Panov\n\nCurrent Issues with Vendor:\n•	No Incident Reporting Tool with vendor\n•	No Technical Reports from vendor\n•	Slow Service Deliveries (response time takes weeks)\n•	Service Level Agreement not clearly defined.\n\nCurrent Technical Issues:\n•	Technical requirements not initially included in School Expansion\n•	Network Cabling requires tidying up\n•	Network Map Diagram\n•	Maintenance of Server Cabinet, Switches, Routers, Modems, Network Connectivity, Windows Desktops and Wireless Access Points\n•	Most issues lies with network connection, quality of connection, slow connection or drop outs. There are times printouts takes a little longer than usual to come out, network connections would drop out, or not connect or slow connection, and programs like Mathletics are taking time to load.\n•	It would be great if the server’s performance is monitored as well as the network connectivity.\n•	Provide Support with Windows Desktops, MacBooks, iPads, SmartBoards, Projector\n•	Some Staff BYOD\n•	Lead IT Projects as requested by the school\n•	Provide/Recommend Hardware Devices and Accessories\n•	Provide/Recommend Software Programs\n•	Maintain Licence Programs\n\nBusiness Requirements:\n•	Provide 2nd level IT Support in 2017\n•	Windows Server Administration and Management\n•	Administer and Monitor Network Connection, Security, LAN, WAN and WAP\n•	Maintain and install network cabling, WAPs, and network ports (Certified Data/Network Cable Installer)\n•	Provide Administration Process Manuals\n•	Provide Basic Technical Knowledge to Staff (Staff training)\n•	How to take advantage and use Computing devices as part of learning\n\nQuestions:\nDo you use an Incident Reporting Tool that customers can also use to log a new incident?\nHow does a customer log a new incident? What is the process?\nCan the customer receive reports on incidents they have logged?\nAre you able to train the staff for any new process you may introduce?\n\nAre you able to provide incident reports to customer on a regular basis ie monthly, quarterly or annually?\n\nCan you please explain your Service Level Deliveries?\nHow do you maintain our Server and Network Integrity?\nDo you have monitoring tools that provides Server and Network status?\n\nWhat’s considered Critical. High, Medium or Low priorities?\nWhat are the Service Level Response Time for Critical, High, Medium or Low priorities?\n\nHow do you maintain data security, perform data backup/restore, perform disaster recoveries and contingencies?\nWhat should customers expect during disaster recovery? How long does it take to bring the system backup? What is the contingency plan in case of failed recoveries or if the problem is not resolved within the guaranteed time?\n\nAre you able to provide/recommend hardware devices and software programs?\nCan you assist with Sentral and Oliver setups?\nCan you assist with software programs that would be beneficial in student learning?\nDo you provide staff training to develop them technically that they may apply in their lessons?\nAre you able to provide stocktake services?\n\nAre you able to provide Administrative and Maintenance Process manuals to customers?\n\nIf we have a networking issue ie wireless connectivity dropouts, can you please explain the process on how we can log the call, and what steps you will take in order to resolve the issue?\n\nWe are currently looking into giving our staff the flexibility to access their files at work from home, do you have any recommendations on how to achieve that?\n\nThe school is mindful of spending, how would you assist the school when it requires a hardware or software?\n\nIf you are to include ICT budget in the school planning in finance, what would you consider that needs to be covered?\nWhat is the cost of acquiring support?\n\n\n--\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on techflare (http://www.techflare.com.au)'),(7549,1933,'original_headers','From: Noel Fabro <contactus@techflare.com.au>\nX-WPCF7-Content-Type: text/plain\nReply-To: noel.fabro@gmail.com\n'),(7550,1933,'session_transcript','smtp:none:none://localhost:25\n\n220 tfhosting04.techflarehosting.com ESMTP Postfix\r\nEHLO localhost\r\n250-tfhosting04.techflarehosting.com\r\n250-PIPELINING\r\n250-SIZE 20971520\r\n250-ETRN\r\n250-STARTTLS\r\n250-AUTH LOGIN CRAM-MD5 PLAIN DIGEST-MD5\r\n250-XFORWARD NAME ADDR PROTO HELO SOURCE PORT IDENT\r\n250-ENHANCEDSTATUSCODES\r\n250-8BITMIME\r\n250 DSN\r\nMAIL FROM:<wordpress@techflare.com.au>\r\n250 2.1.0 Ok\r\nRCPT TO:<contactus@techflare.com.au>\r\n250 2.1.5 Ok\r\nDATA\r\n354 End data with <CR><LF>.<CR><LF>\r\nX-Mailer: Postman SMTP 1.7.2 for WordPress (https://wordpress.org/plugins/postman-smtp/)\r\nX-WPCF7-Content-Type: text/plain\r\nFrom: Noel Fabro <contactus@techflare.com.au>\r\nSender: wordpress@techflare.com.au\r\nTo: contactus@techflare.com.au\r\nReply-To: noel.fabro@gmail.com\r\nSubject: [Techflare Website] - [Quotation]\r\nDate: Thu, 08 Sep 2016 03:40:54 +0000\r\nContent-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8\r\nContent-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable\r\nContent-Disposition: inline\r\nMIME-Version: 1.0\r\n\r\nFrom: Noel Fabro <noel.fabro@gmail.com>=0ASubject: [Techflare Website] -=\r\n [Quotation]=0A=0ACompany Details:=0ACondell park christian School=0A27=\r\n lancelot street=0Acondell park nsw 22